      "review_summary": "The PR adds `armTimer(state)` to cron timer rejection handlers and adds a Vitest regression file for timer re-arming after failures.\n\nPR surface: Source +6, Tests +127. Total +133 across 2 files.\n\nReproducibility: yes. for the narrow source condition: current main's timer catch handlers only log on `onTimer` rejection. The long-uptime macOS stale-wake symptom itself was not reproduced in this read-only review.",
